    <fr:tree show-metadata="true" numbered="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://mkiyoaki.github.io/kiyoaki/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>kiyoaki</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/kiyoaki/</fr:route><fr:title text="Yifei Shi">Yifei Shi</fr:title><fr:taxon>Person</fr:taxon><fr:meta name="institution"><fr:link href="https://www.cam.ac.uk/" type="external">University of Cambridge</fr:link></fr:meta><fr:meta name="orcid">0009-0008-1488-187X</fr:meta><fr:meta name="position">MPhil Student</fr:meta><fr:meta name="external">https://mkiyoaki.github.io</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>I am an MPhil student in <html:em>Advanced Computer Science</html:em> at the <fr:link href="https://www.cam.ac.uk/" type="external">University of Cambridge</fr:link>,
studying with the meta-reasoning limitations and solutions for Large Language Models (LLMs).
Previously I was also a Research Intern at
<fr:link href="https://www.shlab.org.cn/" type="external">Shanghai Artificial Intelligence Laboratory</fr:link>, focusing on AI reasoning and LLMs post-training with formal languages.
I obtained my undergraduate degree of <html:em>Computer Science</html:em> from <fr:link href="https://www.kcl.ac.uk/" type="external">King's College London</fr:link>.
I am also an alumni of <fr:link href="https://deepmind.google/about/education/" type="external">Google DeepMind Education Programme</fr:link>.
</html:p><html:p>My research interests focus on <html:strong>Mechanistic Interpretability</html:strong> and <html:strong>Mathematical Reasoning</html:strong> in Large Language Models.
I aim to build trustworthy AI by dissecting the internal mechanisms of models and aligning their reasoning paths.
Currently, my work focuses on step-level mathematical verification—comparing encoder-based verifiers with generative LLMs—and leveraging reinforcement learning to mitigate shortcut-driven failures and verification loopholes in formal tasks.
</html:p><html:p>This website is built by <fr:link href="https://www.forester-notes.org/index/index.xml" type="external">Forester</fr:link>.
You may navigate this site by pressing <html:code>Ctrl + K</html:code>. </html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

  
    
    
